com.theeyetribe.client

Interface ICalibrationResultListener


  • public interface ICalibrationResultListener
    Callback interface with methods associated to the changes of CalibrationResult. This interface should be implemented by classes that are to receive only changes in CalibrationResult and who are _not_ to perform the calibration process itself.

    Implementing classes should register for updates through GazeManager.addCalibrationResultListener(ICalibrationResultListener).

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void onCalibrationChanged(boolean isCalibrated, CalibrationResult calibResult)
      A notification call back indicating that state of calibration has changed.

    • Method Detail

      • onCalibrationChanged

        void onCalibrationChanged(boolean isCalibrated,
                          CalibrationResult calibResult)
        A notification call back indicating that state of calibration has changed. Implementing classes should update themselves accordingly if needed.
        Parameters:
        isCalibrated - is the EyeTribe Server calibrated?
        calibResult - if calibrated, the currently valid CalibrationResult, otherwise null
